# External operations in lessons (mandatory)

The course author is **learning the stack**. Any step that needs action **outside** the repo (Docker Desktop, cloud dashboards, DNS, third-party accounts) must be spelled out in the **lesson**, not only in code or `.env.example`.

**Full guide:** [`docs/lesson-authoring-guide.md`](docs/lesson-authoring-guide.md#external-operations-вне-репозитория)  
**Template section:** [`docs/lessons/lesson-template.md`](docs/lessons/lesson-template.md) — **External operations (outside the repo)**

## Every lesson must include

Section **`## External operations (outside the repo)`** (or Russian title from template):

1. **Table** — what to do, where (UI/CLI), required for this step or deferred, link to LOCAL_SETUP if shared.
2. **Architecture sketch** — 3–6 sentences: what runs on the laptop, in Docker, in the cloud later; trust boundary in plain language.
3. If **nothing external** — one explicit sentence: «В этом шаге достаточно monorepo + уже поднятого local compose; аккаунты Railway/Vercel/Supabase не нужны.»

## When to call it out (non-exhaustive)

| Category | Examples |
| -------- | -------- |
| Local containers | `docker compose up`, MailDev UI, Postgres port |
| Cloud runtime | Railway, Render, Fly.io — service, env vars, deploy hook |
| Frontend host | Vercel, Netlify — project link, `VITE_*`, SSR vs static |
| Managed data | Supabase, Neon — connection string, migrations vs app |
| Email / auth SaaS | Resend, Clerk — API keys, webhooks (if used) |
| CI / secrets | GitHub Actions secrets, environment protection |
| DNS / TLS | Custom domain, CNAME, certificates (production tracks) |

## Agent behavior

- When **writing or updating** `docs/lessons/lesson-NNN-*.md`, add or refresh **External operations**; do not bury dashboard steps only in Verification one-liners.
- When **planning** a roadmap step that touches infra, note in the step title or verify column if external setup is expected (e.g. «compose + MailDev UI»).
- **Storytelling** stays metaphor-only — no copy-paste of dashboard clicks; the lesson owns the how-to.

## Definition of Done (lesson)

- [ ] Section **External operations** present and accurate for this step.
- [ ] Deferred cloud work named with **future step number** (e.g. «production SMTP — Track 8»).
- [ ] [`LOCAL_SETUP.md`](docs/LOCAL_SETUP.md) updated if new ports, URLs, or compose services.
